XLIX.—L1. Progress of the war in Sicily and the islands. Before the arrival of Sempronius, three Cartha- ginian ships, driven by stress of weather into the straits, had been captured by Hiero’s ships. The safety of Lilybaeum secured by the action of the praetor, M. AEmilius. Arrival of Sempronius; his occupation of Melita. He is recalled by the Senate to join Scipio in the north.
